  "prompt": "A bag contains 5 white, 7 red and 8 black balls. If four balls are drawn one by one without replacement, what is the probability of getting all white balls?",
  "response": "To find the probability of getting four white balls in a row without replacement from a bag containing 5 white, 7 red, and 8 black balls, we need to calculate the probability of drawing a white ball on each draw, given that the previous white balls were drawn.\n\nInitially, there are 5 white balls out of a total of 20 balls. After drawing the first white ball, there are 4 white balls left out of a total of 19 balls. After drawing the second white ball, there are 3 white balls left out of a total of 18 balls. After drawing the third white ball, there are 2 white balls left out of a total of 17 balls.\n\nSo, the probability of drawing four white balls in a row without replacement is:\n\n(5/20) * (4/19) * (3/18) * (2/17) = 1/153\n\nTherefore, the probability of getting all white balls when four balls are drawn one by one without replacement from a bag containing 5 white, 7 red, and 8 black balls is 1/153.",
